Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.11,0:51:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,go from one to 101, you go from 101\Nbackwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.04,0:51:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,How can that be backwards? There we go.\NOh, shake it up. Shake it up, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.83,0:51:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,101 ways to happiness.\NI thought we were talking about peace
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.31,0:51:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,today. I don't want anybody being happy\Nout there.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.96,0:52:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up happiness, man. Give me peace.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.00,0:52:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh,\Nhere's the saddest story I've ever
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.80,0:52:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a great line.\NIt's good to write that right at some
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.83,0:52:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,place, secret place where you can look\Nat it and nobody can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.72,0:52:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours is the saddest story I ever heard.\NI want everybody to make one. A little
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.96,0:52:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,sign.\NYou put it on your mirror at home in the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.24,0:52:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,bathroom. You stick it in the corner of\Nthe mirror. It is an experiment. Do it
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.00,0:52:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,for seven days.\NIf you do it for seven days, you become
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.68,0:53:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a seven dayer.\NAnd I know who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.72,0:53:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it for six days. Cheat. No, I'll know\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.52,0:53:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You put a little sign there. It says,\N"Yours is the saddest story I've ever
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.44,0:53:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,heard." And you put it in the corner of\Nyour mirror. And you will find that your
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.55,0:53:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,life is brightens up instantly.\NWon't cost you anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.76,0:53:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't even charge you a dollar for this.\NWhy? Because it's it it tilts your view
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.68,0:53:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of life into a different direction. just\Nto see that yours is the, you know, that
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.04,0:53:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,kills self-pity.\NIt kills resentment, it kills blame, it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.24,0:53:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,kills all the stuff that makes people\Nmiserable and it gets you back to the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.64,0:53:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,reality that the source of your own\Nhappiness is solely within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.48,0:53:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody can take it away from you. And\Nthat's I was tell all the husband, I
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.59,0:54:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,said, "Listen, you got to do your job.\NDon't let it bother you. I'm ready to
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.52,0:54:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,go. Go ahead. Chop my head off if you\Nlike. I want him to have a good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.55,0:54:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's his job to chop your head off. So\Nwhy complain?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.88,0:54:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,101 ways to peace.\NNumber one.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.96,0:54:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. You got to keep track of the time\Non it. Where are we going to break?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.88,0:54:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> 15 minutes.\N>> How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.72,0:54:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> About 15 minutes.\N>> 15 minutes. Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.64,0:54:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, we can hit cover the history of the\Nworld in 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.96,0:54:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,101 ways to peace. Now, peacefulness\Nthen has to be a decision that you make.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.68,0:54:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Peacefulness can can exist in the right\Nright in the middle of war and
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.24,0:54:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,devastation\Nand catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.11,0:55:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The ways to become develop a peaceful\Nnature. Uh, the first thing to do is to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.35,0:55:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,give up trying to change and control\Nother people.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.20,0:55:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell them how to vote.\NGive up
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.64,0:55:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,questionable advertising. Let go of\Ntrying to change and control others.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.24,0:55:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We always want other people to be\Ndifferent than they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.64,0:55:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can't they be more like like me?\NIf I can't change them, if I'm stuck
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.68,0:55:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with them, well, then at least I can\Ncontrol them. I can control them. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.31,0:55:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see how often your mind would\Nlike to change people and make them
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.59,0:55:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,different.\NThe next big thing to have peace of mind
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.48,0:55:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is to let go to get even.\NYou see that in the political arena,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.04,0:56:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,things the previous administration did,\Nthe new administration has to get into a
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.79,0:56:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a make wrong and a get even because they\Nwant to be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.88,0:56:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you can't never see peace in\Nthe political arena because they're all
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.11,0:56:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,up they're all up to proving others\Nwrong, proving they're right, and trying
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.76,0:56:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to get even for what the previous\Nadministration did 18 years ago or
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.00,0:56:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,something.\NSo let you have to let go wanting to get
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.48,0:56:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,even.\NYou can let go wanting to get even if
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.11,0:56:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand divine justice.\NIf you understand divine justice, it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.28,0:56:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,saves you the bother of getting even\Nbecause everything
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.48,0:56:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,take is taken care of by divine by the\Npresence of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.79,0:56:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All things then karmically\Nhave their own karmic payoff and you
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.92,0:57:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to do anything. It's not\Nnecessarily not necessary to bring down
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.68,0:57:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,your enemies because they will bring\Nthemselves down by their own hand. By
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.35,0:57:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,their own hand, they will do themsel in\Nand then you're not stuck with the
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.35,0:57:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,karma. You see, the minute you get even\Nuh or get even with them or conquer
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.44,0:57:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,them, etc., uh you now have that the\Nkarma of that. If somebody falls over,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.79,0:57:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it's better that they do it of their own\Naccord than you're putting a bullet in
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.28,0:57:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,them.\NIt's impolite to shoot people
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.64,0:57:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,without even asking their permission.\NIt's best to So, if you really want
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.48,0:57:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,peace above all else,\Nthe mind thinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.64,0:57:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind thinks and the spirit knows.\NThe spirit knows. So the spirit knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.68,0:58:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of wine to get even and let go\Nwine to be right. And this is extremely
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.52,0:58:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult in the human condition. In our\Nsociety getting even and being right is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.20,0:58:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,considered a\Ndre.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.92,0:58:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to do that. And the other thing\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.64,0:58:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,goes on is making other people wrong. So\Nif you're right, then other people must
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.40,0:58:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,be wrong.\NThe struggle for moral superiority
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.76,0:58:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of being right is intense.\NSo we learn to practice discernment
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.83,0:58:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than judgmentalism.\NDiscernment and judgmentalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.52,0:58:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Discernment then is interested in\Nfinding out what is the essence of
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.40,0:59:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,something. Discernment is the essence.\NJudgmentalism then is a more seeking the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.55,0:59:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,moral high ground.\NSo we'll go to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.52,0:59:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to make these things come about\Nin your own life is to silence
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.24,0:59:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,opinionation.\NAnd it's not necessary to have an
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.96,0:59:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,opinion about everything.\NIn fact, it's not necessary to have an
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.68,0:59:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,opinion about anything.\NYou don't need an opinion about
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.44,0:59:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,anything.\NIf I said to you, what do you think of
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.92,0:59:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,such and such? You say, "Well, I really\Ndon't have an opinion about it."
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.83,0:59:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Got no opinion? Wishywashy, idiot.\NWhat do you think of our new Supreme
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.68,0:59:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Court justice?\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.48,1:00:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way things are going\Nin our society. This is the way things
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.55,1:00:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,are going. And such a thing is likely to\Nhappen. But when the waves go this way,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.79,1:00:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not likely to happen. So you can\Nstand back from society
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.76,1:00:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of being bobbled around by the\Nwaves.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.11,1:00:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So we learn to be modest with our\Nopinions.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.04,1:00:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We learn to perfect diplomacy,\Ngentility.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.04,1:00:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They really people don't know what the\Nupper classes are. They think people the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.72,1:00:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,upper classes are having jets and big\Nestates and lots of money. They don't
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.31,1:00:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,really know what the upper classes are.\NThe upper classes, everybody's got
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.79,1:00:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,money. It doesn't mean anything.\NEverybody's got a title. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.79,1:00:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The most important thing was the\Ncapacity for diplomacy.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.76,1:01:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uh for diplomacy graciousness.\NI was once put up for one of the
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.72,1:01:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,greatest probably the most exclusive\Nclub in America whose name I I can't
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.92,1:01:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,even mention. And I got to meet all the\Nthe really high people in the world in
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.76,1:01:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the New York City area.\NThe president of this, the president of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.31,1:01:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that. If I told you all the titles,\Nyou'd say you met them. I said, "Yeah."
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.40,1:01:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There was one quality that they had.\N100%. These are the top top people in
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.59,1:01:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the world. Top top. The top of the top.\NEvery one of them was gracious.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.44,1:01:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of them was gracious.\NTo be one of the top people in the
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.55,1:01:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,world. Then the first thing to do is to\Nbe gracious. That means considerate of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.48,1:01:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,others. A sensitivity to others. That\Nthey've been standing a long time.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.48,1:02:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't you like a chair to sit? You've\Nbeen a long time without water. Could I
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.68,1:02:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,get you something to drink?\NThey have to put in another hour or two.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.76,1:02:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, "How about a cup of coffee?"\NThe one thing about the top people in
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.40,1:02:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the world, it was just stunning. Was\Nextremely gracious.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.76,1:02:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Extremely gracious.\NI met the richest, most powerful people
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.24,1:02:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world. And I'd come into their\Noffice and they'd say, "This is Dave
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.40,1:02:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hawkins who I want you to meet." Yes.\NAnd he'd say, "Can I get your cup of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.96,1:02:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,coffee or sit over here where the sun\Nwon't shine in your eyes?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.88,1:02:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the big big foo.\NMake George Soros look like poor."
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.96,1:02:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're\Nsolicitous of your comfort.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.48,1:03:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,be solicitus then of the comfort of\Nothers. This means not just physical
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.35,1:03:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,comfort but their psychological comfort,\Ntheir spiritual comfort. If somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.35,1:03:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,disagrees with with me, I tell them\Nthat's very interesting. I think that's
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.79,1:03:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,great. Disagreeing with me is fine with\Nme. Why? Because I want the person to be
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.68,1:03:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,honest with who they are. All right. I\Ndon't I'm buttering me up with false
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.52,1:03:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,false yes men.\NBe modest with one's opinions. It would
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.20,1:03:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,seem you'll say, "It seems to me at this\Ntime that this is the way it appears to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.28,1:03:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,be." You see, that's flexible.\NIt seems to me a certain way. That
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.28,1:03:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,leaves room for you to move out of the\Nway. So, you become diplomatic and
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.28,1:03:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,gentile.\NYou become gracious and considerate of
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.92,1:03:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,others. People say, "What's all this got\Nto do with God?"
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.16,1:04:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,God is gracious and considerate.\NWhen you get to heaven, he says, "Would
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.83,1:04:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you like to float on this cloud here?\NWould you like to float over the sea?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.76,1:04:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So God comes disguised.\NGod is disguised.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.52,1:04:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to be spiritually advanced\Nto realize the God and everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.03,1:04:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The God and everyone. So the person who\Nsays to you, "Can I get you a cup of
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.59,1:04:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,coffee? Would you like to sit down? You\Nlook like you've been on a long trip."
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.11,1:04:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What's talking to you is not him. What's\Ntalking to you is divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.96,1:04:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's divinity speaking to you.\NWhy? Because divinity is that quality of
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.16,1:05:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness.\NIt's not a personhood. It has no gender,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.35,1:05:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,no age.\Ngentility, consideration for others.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.72,1:05:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also called unconditional love.\NUnconditional lovingness is a concern
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.88,1:05:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for the welfare of others,\Nputting them first that they have the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.20,1:05:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,most comfortable seat. Huh? Be gracious\Nand considerate
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.79,1:05:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep inner serenity as a goal.\NInner serenity as a goal.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.44,1:05:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the point of winning the argument\Nand then you can't sleep all night?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.64,1:05:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I told him off.\NBoy, did I ever tell him off. Dumbass.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.28,1:06:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you keep keep a sense of humor.\NMy secret weapon is a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.64,1:06:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is comical when you look at\Nit a certain way. When you look at it
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.20,1:06:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,from really high space, everything is\Ncomical. Uh here are people struggling
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.76,1:06:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to achieve uh all these things, you\Nknow. Anyway, be modest with your
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.96,1:06:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,opinions. Perfect diplom diplomatic\Nskills and gentility.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.31,1:06:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Be gracious and considerate.\NKeep serenity as a goal.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.72,1:06:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to be wrong or to have no\Nopinion at all. People say, "What do you
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.35,1:06:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,think about that?" You say, "I don't\Nknow. I just haven't thought about it. I
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.24,1:06:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,really can't tell you." People say,\N"Well, that's being wishy-washy."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.11,1:06:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I love being wishy-washy.\NWish she was. She wish she w.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.88,1:07:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think about so and so being\Nout on the Supreme Court? Oh, I think
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.16,1:07:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that's fantastic. At least she ain't out\Nof a job.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.52,1:07:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't collecting unemployment.\NA lot of people where came come from
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.48,1:07:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,where she come from or un unemployment.\NShe ain't on unemployment.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.48,1:07:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Working for a living.\NUh,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.40,1:07:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,another thing you can do and when you're\Nundecided is to calibrate the options
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.35,1:07:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and be flexible.\NAnd this is from an old friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.72,1:07:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not necessary to have an opinion\Non everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.79,1:07:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,An old friend of mine that I came out\Nwest with. And uh, that's his quote. I
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.20,1:07:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,put it in one of the books. Put his name\Nthere. I won't give his name away now.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.88,1:07:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm not giving away his name.\NKeeping it a secret.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.28,1:08:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to have an opinion on\Neverything or on anything. People say,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.48,1:08:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"What do you think about so and so?" And\Nyou say, "Well, I don't know. I just
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.24,1:08:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,haven't given it much thought yet." I'm\Ngoing to think about it after dinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.96,1:08:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to think about it after dinner\Ntonight.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.27,1:08:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We got a lot of to go. I better move\Nalong.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.96,1:08:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, these are all practical. If you\Nwant to live a peaceful life and be
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.67,1:08:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,peaceful, the one of the first rules is\Navoid peace demonstrations.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.75,1:08:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All peace demonstrations are violent.\NThey got dogs, water cannons,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.31,1:08:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,shock machines.\NThey got police all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.04,1:08:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,thugs.\NUsually what goes on at a peace
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.75,1:08:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstration is thugy.\NI can start a riot anywhere
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.27,1:09:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in less than 10 minutes for $50.\NAnybody don't believe me?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.83,1:09:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They know better.\NThe communists learned how to do that,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.64,1:09:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,perfected the art of it. For $50, you\Ncan start a riot anywhere. I'll tell you
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.27,1:09:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,how. In case you want to start a riot,\Ndon't have to be a commie.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.08,1:09:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to start a riot, you go to the\Nnearest lowass bar.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.23,1:09:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I got 50 bucks here, fellas.\NNow, what I want you to do, there's some
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.64,1:09:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,badass guys out there that stole my car\Nand my girlfriend, and I want you to
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.44,1:09:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,give them a good poke in the nose and\Nteach them a lesson. Any takers?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.80,1:09:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,$10 a piece. I can get five guys to\Nleave any bar anytime.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.19,1:10:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have two shots in a beer when\Nyou get back. Okay. Okay. SOP.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.67,1:10:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Next thing you know, there's a riot on\Nthe street. Then the call call the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.44,1:10:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,police. I can start a riot anywhere in\Nfive minutes flat. The communists
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.28,1:10:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,perfected the technique of this\Nspontaneous demonstrations.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.67,1:10:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All spontaneous demonstrations are\Nstaged.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.00,1:10:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't staged, why would they all\Nbe there?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.60,1:10:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would 50 people be on a street\Ncorner?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.08,1:10:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people is there standing in the\Naverage New York street cover corner?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.32,1:10:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,One or two? Five maybe. Not 50. How do\Nyou get 50 people on a street corner?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.88,1:10:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You get get it by organized\Ncommunity organizing.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.12,1:11:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called barroom organizing. Nearest\Nbarroom. We'll get you demonstrators in
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.23,1:11:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,two minutes. And demonstrators love\Ndemonstrating. So they'll pull in more
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.67,1:11:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrators. Next thing you know, the\Nknuckles are going and the police are
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.84,1:11:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,there. It's wonderful excitement.\NEverybody's adrenaline goes up.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.60,1:11:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's having a good time.\NSo if you want to be peaceful, avoid
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.60,1:11:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,peace demonstrations because they are\Ntoo violent.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.67,1:11:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They got police dogs, water cannons.\NAnd here, this is useful. And I'll leave
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.08,1:11:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you with this thought while we take a\Nbreak. We're going to take a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.71,1:11:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All of you who pine to be beautiful and\Nrich and all, remember that Socrates was
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.48,1:11:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,short and ugly.\NIt's okay to be short and ugly.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.28,1:12:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates was short and ugly. He wasn't\Ntall and handsome.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.12,1:12:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates became world famous for\Ncenturies.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.36,1:12:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He was neither tall nor handsome nor\Nrich.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.15,1:12:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, we'll convene again. How\Nlong?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.19,1:12:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Um about 11:30.\N>> How soon is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.08,1:12:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> 15 minutes.\N>> 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.92,1:12:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Have one for the road.
